import pycld2 

def guess_lang(text):
    try:
        reliable, _, langs = pycld2.detect(text, isPlainText=True, hintLanguage='en')
        if reliable:
            return langs[0][0]
    except pycld2.error as e:
        pass
    return np.NaN

# guess what language was used.(pycld2)
# It is a function with plain text, not a website, text probably is English (hintLanguage='en')
# If answer is reliable (if reliable:), take the first language off the list (return langs[0][0])
# If answer is not reliable, print NaN (Not a Number, missing value)
# descending order 
#  except pycld2.error as e: pass (means that if there is an error in pycld2, just skip it)

def termf(texts):
    return Counter(concat(map(tokenize, tqdm(texts))))

# tqdm: show progressing bar, map: give a fn and seq (how many words in the, list,.....)
# list of reviews of list of tokens(words)

In [69]:
def G2(f12, f1, f2, N):
    return llr.llr_root(f12, f1-f12, f2-f12, N-f1-f2+f12)

def pmi(f12, f1, f2, N):
    return log2(f12) + log2(N) - log2(f1) - log2(f2)

# association filthy and bad review
# how many words in bad review
# N= total size

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from wordcloud import WordCloud
In [77]:
def cloud(freqs, k=200):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10,10))
    items = dict(freqs.sort_values(ascending=False).head(k))
    wc = WordCloud(width=1000, 
                   height=1000, 
                   background_color='white').generate_from_frequencies(items)
    plt.axis('off')
    plt.imshow(wc, interpolation='bilinear')
    plt.show()

# plug pandas into wordcloud
